###### Syria Joint Bases

*   Main articles: [Operation Inherent Resolve § Military bases](/Operation_Inherent_Resolve), and [American-led intervention in the Syrian civil war](/American-led_intervention_in_the_Syrian_civil_war)
*   Landing zone at [Al-Tanf](/Al-Tanf_(U.S._military_base)), [Syria](/Syria).
*   Approximately 1,500–2,000 U.S. forces were in [Syria](/Syria), dispersed across 12 facilities, serving as training bases for Kurdish rebels. These forces withdrew to western Iraq in October 2019. The [Pentagon](/The_Pentagon), however, reportedly planned to leave 150 Special Operations forces at [al-Tanf](/Al-Tanf_(U.S._military_base)) to train [Free Syrian Army](/Free_Syrian_Army) rebels. An additional 200 U.S. soldiers were to remain in eastern Syria, near the oil fields, to deter advances by the [Islamic State](/Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant), the [Syrian government](/Politics_of_Syria), and [Russian](/Russia) forces. The presence in Syria is considered "illegal" by the Syrian government, lacking their consent.

